               <head>Historical anecdotes</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kalām al-mulūk by Yūsuf Lāhījī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85067900" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15581-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7644">Yūsuf Lāhījī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7644" type="supplied">یوسف لاهیجی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1077">Kalām al-mulūk</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1077">کلام الملوک</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A collection of historical anecdotes compiled by Yūsuf Lāhījī and dedicated (see f. 3r) to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_51026511" role="pat">Fatḥ ‘Alī  Shah Qājār</persName> (reg. 1212-50/1797-1834). Includes numerous narratives relating to the Imams and scholars of the Shī‘a and to renowned saints.
                        </p>
                        <p>Other contents: f. 340v, notes of financial transactions, with dates.</p>
                        <p>Undated.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation />
                  </msItem>
